       It seems to me that the game is almost unplayable as it is. They need to fix this stuff first before adding any nw content for uber or casual player. Then for the next expansion they need to do 2 things. First, give the ubers their needed upgrades in raid content. Balance the classes better so that all have a role in the high end and not totally dependent on the almighty trio. Next, they need to make existing content more accessible for the existing non-ubers. I have my VT key and hated the boring camps. WHAT DID IT PROVE? Only that I had enough time to play. Increase the drop rates on key items so that people will actually not hate getting them. Change the formula for pulling in non-flagged guildies maybe down to 10% or eliminate it entirely. I can hear the ubers bitching now that they had to earn their right to be in Time or wherever. I have always thought that your actual ability to play should count a lot more than your ability to just be able to play a lot. If I were allowed a third request it would be that zones have places where single groups can paly and have a chance at some useable gear while still getting some experience. BOT was always so crowded because it fit that bill. Why not make more of those zones rather than cram everyone all into one zone.<br>
    I am so sllep deprived now to the point of incoherence (well past it actually), but if at least these bugs dont get fixed I have to rethink playing at all which  hurts cause I really like my bard.<br>
