<br>
Between raids...<br>
<br>
We do casual gaming.<br>
<br>
We mess around in various zones for fun and/or exp.<br>
<br>
We go back to &quot;old&quot; content, and see what we are capable of killing with as small a force as possible.<br>
<br>
We solo.<br>
<br>
We hang out and kill stuff with friends.<br>
<br>
We get into pickup groups.<br>
<br>
We kill stuff to gather tradeskill supplies or sellables.<br>
<br>
We do old quests that we never completed, and would really like to do for fun (or to just clear out 329024 bank slots).<br>
<br>
We make new chars, and level them up.<br>
<br>
Sometimes, they are twinks - geared to the 9's and PL'd up fast.<br>
<br>
Other times, they are just new chars - played straight, with no extra gear or help.<br>
<br>
And when we do most of these things?  The casual gamers get all pissed off at us, because, you see, we are high end gamers.  That means we should be past all of the &quot;old&quot; content, which is to say that casual gamers want the high end players to leave everything alone so that casual gamers can play with it.  <br>
<br>
I've been messing around in Velks a lot recently.  There's a guy in there who spent 3 days telling me how uber and amazing my guild was.  The 4th day, I was in the camp that he wanted.  Suddenly I was assailed with bitter, snide remarks about how I shouldn't even be there, but I'm being greedy because I'm so uber.<br>
<br>
We high end gamers get told to move on...we don't belong in the lower content areas.  We've already had our chance, and have no right to have a wack at the stuff again.  And we get told that we are abusing our uberness when we do go after old stuff for whatever reason (fun, sellables, TS supply runs, etc).<br>
<br>
Do high end gamers know the casual side of the game?  Yes. <p>~Lorilei<br>
