Ldon was such a good concept, it needs extending.  Something that initially scaled so well with levels, then gear/aa's (when you started doing hard ldons) was perfect in my humble opinion.  <br>
If there was ldon type adv's for old content (Velks is probably a good example, or even something like HoT) for a group, that gave some reward for doing, scaled appropriately for the group in much the way ldon did, I think that would be a pretty good start.<br>
Something that ties in to old content, not just eliminates it (as every expansion is forced todo). <br>
I don't know, cleverer people than me can surely come up with stuff, but it just seems that there's getting ever so fewer things todo now.  Tradeskills? Done as much of them as is fun (would never go through all that again on another char).  Old content? Aye, get the moans from others as to why I'm there (even if it is for tradeskill stuff).<br>
Ldon really improved the game for me.  Good xp, decent loot, SOMETHING TO AIM FOR!  After running through the same dungeons time and time again, I'm up for something new (not more dungeons in the same themes, seriously, there's a whole stack of lore from around the world that could be expanded on, with items that reflect the type of zones.  A theme in Kunark, in Velious, in Luclin (maybe even LoY, gotta be something done to get people there)).  Something todo for 1hr while waiting for everyone to log on for the raid, or to wind down from the raid (if it wiped because of a stupid bug).<br>
Actually, that said, main thing that's getting to me lately is the last gfx upgrade.  Getting stuck on things in pok/advs/anywhere is starting to get seriously tired.  Can usually MMM out if normal travelling, it's got me killed too often in an adv.<br>
Like I said, there's cleverer people out there than me, please, just give me something todo/look forward to.<br>
